            <mixed-citation publication-type="book">Zimmerman HJ. Diuretic drugs. Drugs used in cardiovascular disease. In, Zimmerman HJ. Hepatotoxicity: the adverse effects of drugs and other chemicals on the liver. 2nd ed. Philadelphia: Lippincott, 1999, pp. 662-4.<annotation><p><italic toggle="yes">(Expert review of hepatotoxicity of diuretics published in 1999 mentions that clinically apparent liver injury due to diuretics is rare; cholestatic jaundice with features of hypersensitivity have been reported with some thiazide diuretics).</italic></p></annotation></mixed-citation>
